Description: Papyrus (five fragments) written with black ink with demotic legal text on recto (remains of 5 ll.), verso blank. Thompson's MS Catalogue: "Fragment of a contract or other document relating to the purchase of land. Date none [late Ptolemaic]. Origin Siut (?)".
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (381134) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/381134)
Acquisition notes: Purchased from M. Nahman. Cf. the additional sheets at the end of Thompson's MS Catalogue, titled "B.M. Nahman Papyri (1923)".
